have a separate method that handles toggling:</p>
<pre><code class="lang-java">public void toggleClaw() {
  Value oppValue = clawSolenoid.get() == Value.kForward ? Value.kReverse : Value.kForward;
  clawSolenoid.set(oppValue);
}
</code></pre>
<p>and inside the <code>RobotContainer.java</code> create a button binding that lets you call that:</p>
<pre><code class="lang-java">Trigger rightBumper = new JoystickButton(xb, XboxController.Button.kRightBumper.value);
// replace &lt;subsystem&gt; with wherever the toggle method lives.
rightBumper.onTrue(new InstandCommand(&lt;subsystem&gt;::toggleClaw, &lt;subsystem&gt;)); 
</code></pre>","post_number":2,"post_type":1,"posts_count":7,"updated_at":"2023-02-16T22:28:41.062Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":47,"readers_count":46,"score":9.4,"yours":false,"topic_id":427075,"topic_slug":"toggle-switch-locking-in-on-mode-coding-java","display_username":"mahim","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":3,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":"","bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":29279,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_custom_fields":{"user_field_4":""},"post_url":"/t/toggle-switch-locking-in-on-mode-coding-java/427075/2","custom_user_title":null,"reactions":[],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":0,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":null},{"id":3147035,"name":"Tim Sieberg","username":"tsieberg","avatar_template":"/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/t/a88e57/{size}.png","created_at":"2023-02-16T22:09:23.831Z","cooked":"<p>Mahim‚Äôs answer is correct and simple.  Alternatively, if you want to make your existing code work, I‚Äôm guessing you need to define your clawCheck variable as a static variable.</p>","post_number":3,"post_type":1,"posts_count":7,"updated_at":"2023-02-16T22:09:23.831Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":40,"readers_count":39,"score":23.0,"yours":false,"topic_id":427075,"topic_slug":"toggle-switch-locking-in-on-mode-coding-java","display_username":"Tim Sieberg","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":n