<p><a class="mention" href="/u/mahim">@Mahim</a>‚Äôs answer uses command-based, which is irrelevant to OP who is using timed. Answers that are basically ‚Äúrewrite your entire code‚Äù aren‚Äôt helpful.</p>
</blockquote>
</aside>
<p>If that‚Äôs the case then i would rather suggest keeping track of the button state instead of manually using a counter to keep track.</p>
<pre data-code-wrap="java"><code class="lang-java">// declare this somewhere outside the scope of the toggling
boolean lastPressed = false;
</code></pre>
<p>now your toggling can look something like this inside teleop perioidic:</p>
<pre data-code-wrap="java"><code class="lang-java">@Override
public void teleopPeriodic() {
  boolean currentPressed = xb.getRightBumperPressed();
  if (currentPressed &amp;&amp; !lastPressed) {
    clawSolenoid.toggle();
  }
  lastPressed = currentPressed;
}
</code></pre>
<p>The reason you would want to keep track of the button state is so you can toggle state JUST when button goes from false ‚Üí true.</p>
